description:
&lt;p&gt;Calling all Nurses. Do you want skills that will further your career? Do you want to enhance your organisational, clinical and holistic skills? Do you want to understand and work with Dual Diagnosis?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are Path 2 Recovery (P2R)- the drug and alcohol misuse service for Bedfordshire. We are a diverse, high energy team. P2R is responsible for 700 prescribed clients. Total caseload for P2R is 1200, approx a third are dual diagnosis.&lt;br /&gt;You will join us at an exciting time as we drive to build on our recent successes as one of the top performing services in the country, securing 2 additional years to deliver services. ( Sept 2022) You will be both an enthusiastic and dynamic, managing a caseload offering high-quality, safe, patient-centred care and treatment to drug and alcohol misusers&lt;br /&gt;We offer a strong clinical team (and a path to your Mentorship Training and perhaps to NMP if youre interested?). This could be your next step?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are qualified perhaps newly, probably under 2 years? And looking to enhance your skill base - we look forward to meeting you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For questions and queries please email: Sharon.hawley1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Hawley , Sharon.hawley1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
